Connection Strings:
In .NET apps, App Service connection strings override those in Web.config.

In app service
Always On: Keeps the app loaded even without traffic; required for WebJobs.

for an app service u can enable diagnostic logging to gather insights about app behavior.

SSL/TLS Certificates:
SSL certificates can be installed for secure communication.
They are stored and managed within Azure Key Vault or directly in the App Service.

IIS (Internet Information Services):
A web server for hosting ASP.NET applications, primarily for Windows-based or uncontainerized apps